1.10
log
@update kerberosV to Heimdal 1.5.2 using BSD Makefiles based
on the ones from FreeBSD

This is getting commited now so that we can patch it up
fast in the tree.
There are known regressions so please don't try to build
this on your own now, please wait for the next available
snapshot.

If however you would still want to build it, make sure
build and install everything in the tools directory first.

This is not the full commit yet because there are several
subdirectories.
@
text
@d1 1
a1 1
# $OpenBSD$
d7 2
a8 2
LDADD=	-lkafs5 -lkrb5 -lheimntlm -lroken ${LIBVERS} -lpthread \
	-lasn1 -lcrypto -lcom_err -lhx509 -lheimbase -lwind
@


1.9
log
@The heimdal code switched to using DES from libcrypto when 0.7.2
was imported over four years ago, so we don't need to link libdes
for kerberos anymore.

ok mikeb@@ deraadt@@
@
text
@d1 1
a1 4
# $OpenBSD: Makefile,v 1.8 2003/07/14 16:14:44 mho Exp $

KRBDEPTH=../..
.include <${.CURDIR}/../../Makefile.inc>
d4 5
a8 1
MLINKS=	kinit.1 kauth.1
d10 1
a10 4
SRCS=	kinit.c
SRCS+=	${PRINTVER}

.PATH:	${KRB5SRC}/kuser
d12 1
a12 4
DPADD+=	${LIBKRB5} ${LIBCRYPTO}
LDADD+=	-lkrb5 -lcrypto

.include <bsd.prog.mk>
@


